WEBVTT

00:01.877 --> 00:04.346
GIDEON: Zombie attack? Never works.
They don't take orders.

00:04.546 --> 00:07.891
Blood rain? Ew! Mess up my suit.
Heh, no, thank you.

00:08.090 --> 00:09.468
Demon caterpillars?

00:09.843 --> 00:13.814
Drat! There must be a perfect way
to exact vengeance on the Pines family.

00:14.014 --> 00:16.938
It's not enough to harm 'em,
I need to take something from 'em.

00:17.142 --> 00:19.486
Something that'll give me
ultimate power!

00:19.686 --> 00:20.903
Wait, of course!

00:21.980 --> 00:23.402
(WHISPERS) It's perfect.

00:26.527 --> 00:28.950
MAN: <i>(ON</i> TV) <i>You've gone too far
this time, Duck-tective.</i>

00:29.154 --> 00:31.907
-(QUACKING HEARD ON TV)
-(DOORBELL RINGS)

00:32.115 --> 00:34.584
Welcome to a world of mystery!

00:34.785 --> 00:36.082
Stan Pines?

00:36.286 --> 00:38.414
The tax collector! You found me!

00:38.622 --> 00:39.874
L-la!

00:40.082 --> 00:42.631
(PANTING)

00:42.834 --> 00:43.960
(GRUNTING)

00:44.169 --> 00:45.796
Which one of these is the trap door?

00:46.004 --> 00:50.134
Mr. Pines, I'm from the
Winninghouse Coupon Savers Contest

00:50.342 --> 00:54.142
and you are our big winner!

00:55.514 --> 00:56.481
Eh?

00:56.682 --> 00:58.355
My one and only dream,

00:58.559 --> 01:01.062
which was to possess money,
has come true!

01:01.270 --> 01:02.897
We're rich! I'm gonna get a butler!

01:03.105 --> 01:04.732
I'm gonna buy a talking horse!

01:04.940 --> 01:08.160
- Just sign here for the money.
- You bet!

01:08.360 --> 01:09.282
L-la!

01:09.486 --> 01:10.908
Stanford, you fool!

01:11.113 --> 01:15.459
You just signed over
the Mystery Shack to widdle 0l' me!

01:15.659 --> 01:16.956
Ah-ha! Cha-cha.

01:17.160 --> 01:18.537
-(BOTH GASP)
- Little 0l' me.

01:18.745 --> 01:22.124
Uh, you might want to
take another look there.

01:22.332 --> 01:26.963
"The Shack is hereby signed over
to... Suck a lemon, little man."

01:29.172 --> 01:30.264
How dare you!

01:30.465 --> 01:31.341
(LAUGHING)

01:31.550 --> 01:34.645
I am not a threat to be taken lightly.

01:34.845 --> 01:36.188
(STRAINING)

01:36.388 --> 01:38.311
Come here, hon, I need your arms.

01:38.849 --> 01:43.025
I'll get you, Stanford Pines.
I'll get you all!

01:45.105 --> 01:46.823
- Want to see what else is on TV?
- Yeah, okay.

01:47.024 --> 01:47.900
- Yeah, all right.
- It could be fun.

01:48.108 --> 01:49.200
My favorite part is the theme song.

01:49.401 --> 01:52.701
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

02:31.234 --> 02:33.862
Little guy to black space nine.

02:34.071 --> 02:37.792
It's a "Pawn," that's not your color,
and stop stealing the tiny horses.

02:37.991 --> 02:40.744
They like it better in here.
Don't you, babies?

02:40.952 --> 02:41.953
(WHINNIES)

02:42.162 --> 02:44.415
- And checkmate!
- What?

02:44.623 --> 02:46.216
BED]

02:46.416 --> 02:47.383
DIPPER: Oh!

02:47.584 --> 02:48.961
Dipper wins again!

02:49.169 --> 02:51.171
Yo, Mabel, can you pass
me that brain in the jar?

02:51.380 --> 02:52.848
- The lady one.
- I got it.

02:53.048 --> 02:54.425
Thanks, but Mabel's taller.

02:54.633 --> 02:55.805
What? No, she's not.

02:56.009 --> 02:57.977
We're the same height.
We've always been.

02:58.178 --> 02:59.395
Better check again, dude.

03:06.520 --> 03:08.818
Yeah. She's got exactly
one millimeter on you.

03:09.022 --> 03:10.114
- What?
- Whoa!

03:10.315 --> 03:11.692
Don't you see
what's happening, Dipper?

03:11.858 --> 03:16.864
This millimeter is just the beginning.
I'm evolving into the superior sibling.

03:17.072 --> 03:19.040
Bigger! Stronger!

03:19.241 --> 03:20.493
Like some kind of alpha twin.

03:20.701 --> 03:23.454
Alpha twin! Alpha twin!

03:23.662 --> 03:26.006
Come on, guys,
nobody even uses millimeters.

03:26.206 --> 03:27.924
It only makes you
taller than me in Canada.

03:28.125 --> 03:30.378
You know, Dipper,
I've always wanted a little brother.

03:30.585 --> 03:34.260
Who knew I already had one! Yeah!

03:34.464 --> 03:37.183
I was awoken by the sound of mockery.
Where is it?

03:37.384 --> 03:38.931
Show me the object of ridicule!

03:39.136 --> 03:41.480
- I'm taller than Dipper.
- By one millimeter!

03:41.680 --> 03:44.854
Hey-hey.
Don't get "short" with your sister.

03:45.058 --> 03:49.234
Now, Grunkle Stan,
I hope you don't think "little" of him!

03:49.438 --> 03:53.113
Yeah! And he's short!

03:53.316 --> 03:55.159
Dude, maybe you should
lay off a tiny bit.

03:55.360 --> 03:57.988
Ha! "Tiny!" Soos is in on it now!

04:00.699 --> 04:01.916
No, no, I didn't mean that.

04:02.117 --> 04:05.246
Dipper will forget.
He's got a three-two-one...

04:05.454 --> 04:07.832
- Short term memory!
- Short term memory!

04:08.039 --> 04:10.963
Pow! We are on fire!

04:11.168 --> 04:13.011
Ow! Ooh. That's... Ah!

04:13.211 --> 04:14.713
I high-five hard.

04:15.922 --> 04:18.596
Uh! Stupid Mabel. I'm not short!

04:20.051 --> 04:21.394
(STRAINING)

04:21.595 --> 04:22.517
Oh, come on!

04:25.015 --> 04:27.484
There's gotta be some way to get taller.

04:27.684 --> 04:28.901
Let's see...

04:30.812 --> 04:34.191
"Legends of miniature buffalo and
giant squirrels have led me to believe

04:34.399 --> 04:37.949
"there are height-altering properties
hidden deep within the forest."

04:38.153 --> 04:39.120
Hmm.

04:39.321 --> 04:43.827
(GROANS)

04:45.494 --> 04:46.666
Oh.

04:50.582 --> 04:51.458
Whoa!

04:56.963 --> 04:58.055
(EAGLE SHRIEKING)

04:58.256 --> 05:01.135
- Huh? Oh.
-(GROWLING)

05:01.343 --> 05:05.519
Is that mountain lion tiny
or just far away in perspective?

05:05.722 --> 05:08.521
Perspective! Perspective!
(SCREAMS)

05:13.647 --> 05:15.490
(PURRS)

05:15.690 --> 05:17.613
It still hurts, but less!

05:23.281 --> 05:24.328
Whoa!

05:30.914 --> 05:31.961
What the heck.

05:44.636 --> 05:48.732
Smaller.

05:48.932 --> 05:51.151
Bigger.

05:51.351 --> 05:52.648
Too big!

05:52.853 --> 05:55.902
I've been buying big clothes.
I'll grow into them.

05:56.106 --> 05:59.235
Hey, guys.
Notice anything different about me?

05:59.442 --> 06:01.865
Holy hot-sauce!
You've grown an extra millimeter!

06:02.028 --> 06:03.200
What?

06:07.158 --> 06:09.035
What can I say, sis? Growth spurt.

06:09.244 --> 06:12.248
Yeah, mine happened first.
I'm gonna be taller in the end.

06:12.455 --> 06:14.253
- It's science, Dipper.
- What?

06:14.457 --> 06:18.132
- But, we're the same height now.
- Alpha twin! Alpha twin!

06:18.336 --> 06:19.258
Oh, yeah?

06:19.462 --> 06:23.183
Something tells me I've got another
growth spurt coming on right now.

06:28.138 --> 06:29.435
Give it up, Dipper!

06:29.639 --> 06:31.266
(GASPS)

06:31.474 --> 06:32.851
What happened?

06:33.059 --> 06:34.402
You know, puberty and stuff.

06:34.603 --> 06:37.823
It doesn't make any sense!
Just a second ago you were...

06:38.023 --> 06:41.527
Wait a minute! This is some kind
of magicy thing, isn't it?

06:41.735 --> 06:43.282
Was it a wizard or something?

06:43.486 --> 06:45.705
There's a wizard in this closet,
isn't there? Isn't there?

06:45.906 --> 06:47.158
What? No!

06:47.365 --> 06:49.788
You're telling me
there is not a wizard in this closet?

06:49.993 --> 06:52.837
You're telling me
that if I open this door right now...

06:53.038 --> 06:57.009
Fine! Open it!

06:57.208 --> 07:00.303
An invisible wizard! Really, Dipper?

07:00.462 --> 07:02.214
(DOORBELL RINGS)

07:02.422 --> 07:06.723
- Oy, you.
- Howdy, Stanford! Listen closely.

07:06.927 --> 07:11.148
Inside this jar, I have
1,000 cursed Egyptian super-termites.

07:11.348 --> 07:14.648
Hand over the deed to your property
or I'll smash this jar with a bat

07:14.851 --> 07:17.775
and they'll devour this shack
with you inside.

07:17.979 --> 07:20.198
- Hey, what's that?
- Huh?

07:20.398 --> 07:24.119
(GASPS) Oh, no! Get it off!

07:24.319 --> 07:26.822
Hey, Soos, get in here!
I want to take pictures of this!

07:27.030 --> 07:30.705
Y'all may have won the battle.
But mark my words, Stanford!

07:30.909 --> 07:34.038
Your family has a weak spot,
and I'm gonna find it.

07:34.245 --> 07:36.043
Ahhh! My hair!

07:36.247 --> 07:41.970
Does he only respond to incantations?
Expecto Wizarium! Wizzle! Wizar...

07:42.128 --> 07:43.129
It's not a wizard!

07:43.338 --> 07:46.262
I grew myself
using this magic flashlight!

07:46.466 --> 07:49.185
Let me see that thing!

07:49.386 --> 07:51.730
I'll be back for you later!

07:51.930 --> 07:53.227
(DIPPER GROANS)

07:58.561 --> 08:00.814
(CAR ALARM BLARING)

08:01.022 --> 08:01.864
BOTH: Huh?

08:05.527 --> 08:08.576
- Aah!
- It's okay. It can shrink things, too.

08:08.780 --> 08:10.999
- Normal-hand-karate-chop!
- Hey!

08:14.327 --> 08:17.001
(GRUNTING)

08:17.163 --> 08:19.336
(SCREAMS)

08:19.541 --> 08:21.964
Whoa!

08:22.168 --> 08:24.421
Hey, give it back!

08:24.629 --> 08:25.721
MABEL: Never!

08:25.922 --> 08:27.799
(BOTH GRUNTING)

08:28.008 --> 08:32.764
Curse the Pines family!
Curse Stan! Curse Dipper! Curse...

08:32.971 --> 08:36.976
My, my, what delightful manner
of doohickery is this?

08:37.183 --> 08:38.856
Maybe he didn't see us use it

08:39.059 --> 08:43.440
and doesn't know it's a magic flashlight
that can grow and shrink things.

08:43.648 --> 08:46.618
- Really?
- Click. Boop.

08:46.818 --> 08:48.115
BOTH: No, no, no!

08:52.574 --> 08:55.919
(BELLOWING LAUGH)

09:03.168 --> 09:05.717
(AIR HORN BLOWS)

09:05.920 --> 09:08.673
Friends, I wish I was a highway
so I could have the honor

09:08.882 --> 09:13.353
of being rode upon by automobiles
as fine as these ones right ch'er.

09:13.553 --> 09:14.520
(SNARLS)

09:14.721 --> 09:16.394
Engine possum at no extra charge.

09:16.598 --> 09:17.941
I want that there car!

09:18.141 --> 09:20.485
(ALL CHEERING)

09:20.685 --> 09:23.404
Say there, son, what's in the jar?

09:23.605 --> 09:25.573
That's my widdle secret!

09:25.774 --> 09:27.276
Aw!

09:27.484 --> 09:28.485
(GIGGLES)

09:28.693 --> 09:30.866
Mouth-breathing fools.

09:32.864 --> 09:33.865
Mother.

09:41.581 --> 09:42.628
(BOTH GRUNTING)

09:42.832 --> 09:44.175
You two.

09:44.375 --> 09:45.922
What are you going to do with us?

09:46.127 --> 09:50.428
Why, Mabel, I wouldn't hurt a hair
on your itty bitty head.

09:50.590 --> 09:52.433
If you agree to be my queen!

09:52.634 --> 09:55.183
We live in a democracy. And never!

09:55.386 --> 09:58.435
Maybe you'll
change your mind after this.

09:58.640 --> 10:01.268
No! I will fight you until the day I...

10:01.476 --> 10:04.650
(GASPS) Gummy Koalas!

10:04.854 --> 10:07.198
(MUNCHING)

10:07.398 --> 10:09.241
As for you, DOV,

10:10.610 --> 10:14.114
tell me, how exactly did you
come upon this magic item, hmm?

10:14.322 --> 10:18.623
Did somebody tell you about it?
Did you read about it somewhere?

10:21.579 --> 10:24.423
- Lean closer and I'll tell you.
- Well, don't mind if I...

10:24.624 --> 10:26.501
-(AIR HORN BLASTS)
- Aah!

10:26.709 --> 10:29.428
(HEAVY BREATHING)

10:29.629 --> 10:31.927
I could squash you right now!

10:34.759 --> 10:38.480
Steel yourself, Gideon.
You can use them.

10:38.680 --> 10:40.933
You can use them.

10:41.141 --> 10:45.362
Soos, this maze of mirrors is your
best idea that I'm taking credit for yet!

10:45.562 --> 10:48.315
We're gonna make a fortune!

10:48.523 --> 10:51.402
- Have my ears always been this big?
-(PHONE RINGS)

10:51.609 --> 10:52.861
LN' Q “N I“ <i>'</i> a

10:57.657 --> 10:59.000
One day.

10:59.200 --> 11:00.622
-(PHONE CONTINUES RINGING)
-(GROANS)

11:00.827 --> 11:01.669
GIDEON: (OVER PHONE)
<i>Stanford Pines.</i>

11:01.870 --> 11:04.749
Listen to me very closely,
I have your niece and nephew.

11:04.956 --> 11:07.050
Hand over the deed
to the Mystery Shack right now

11:07.250 --> 11:09.753
or great harm will befall them!

11:09.961 --> 11:12.089
- This is Gideon, by the way.
-(STAN LAUGHING)

11:12.297 --> 11:14.641
Oh, yeah.
This has gotta be your worst plot yet.

11:14.841 --> 11:15.637
They're fine.

11:15.842 --> 11:17.844
I saw them playing
in the yard minutes ago.

11:18.052 --> 11:20.350
I have them in my possession!
You don't believe me?

11:20.555 --> 11:22.557
I will text you a photo.

11:22.765 --> 11:26.065
"Text" me a "photo"?
Now you're not even speaking English.

11:26.269 --> 11:27.270
GIDEON: But...

11:27.478 --> 11:29.151
Hello? Hello!

11:29.355 --> 11:30.902
(GRUNTS)

11:31.107 --> 11:32.154
Ahhh!

11:32.358 --> 11:36.864
(MANIACAL LAUGHTER)

11:37.071 --> 11:39.699
What am I doing? I don't need ransom.

11:39.908 --> 11:45.711
I have this! I'll shrink Stan
and take the Shack for myself!

11:45.914 --> 11:47.541
Y'all will be helpless to stop me!

11:47.749 --> 11:50.923
And if any of you
step out of line, smash!

11:52.879 --> 11:54.677
(CACKLES)

11:54.881 --> 11:58.727
BUD: Gideon, the ice cream
truck is here!

11:58.927 --> 12:00.474
Oh. Coming!

12:00.678 --> 12:02.180
(GIGGLES)

12:05.475 --> 12:08.445
Guard them, Cheekums. I'm coming!

12:10.563 --> 12:12.281
(SQUEAKING)

12:16.486 --> 12:18.159
We got to get out of here and save Stan.

12:18.363 --> 12:21.207
I know! I will see you later.

12:21.407 --> 12:22.659
Okay, how are we going to do this?

12:22.867 --> 12:26.121
Gideon's got magic
and like a zillion inches on us.

12:26.329 --> 12:28.878
On the bright side, at least we're finally
the same height again.

12:29.082 --> 12:31.585
Actually...

12:31.793 --> 12:35.639
(DIPPER GRUNTING)

12:35.797 --> 12:37.140
You're still taller?

12:37.340 --> 12:38.887
Argh! How did this happen?

12:39.092 --> 12:40.969
I guess it's another mystery.

12:41.177 --> 12:44.056
Just another reason
we gotta get that flashlight back.

12:48.351 --> 12:51.104
Cheekums, to freedom!

12:51.312 --> 12:53.861
To freedom!

12:54.065 --> 12:58.787
Aw! You're just a big ol' dummy-dum!

12:58.987 --> 12:59.863
I have a plan.

13:11.457 --> 13:15.803
(MUNCHING)

13:16.004 --> 13:17.256
Clean me!

13:17.755 --> 13:22.101
Father, could you give widdle ol' me
a wide to the Mystery Shack?

13:22.302 --> 13:23.804
Oh, I'd love to, sugar-pie,

13:24.012 --> 13:27.437
but I have a heck
of a lot of cars to sell, I do.

13:27.640 --> 13:28.562
(LAUGHS)

13:28.766 --> 13:32.566
No, no! Don't tickle me! No!

13:33.604 --> 13:36.778
Never! Never tickle me!
What have I told you? What have I...

13:36.983 --> 13:38.951
Look at me. What have I told you?

13:39.152 --> 13:41.496
Tickling is no laughing matter.

13:41.696 --> 13:44.074
- There we go.
- Do you still need a ride?

13:44.282 --> 13:47.832
I'll just take the bus!

13:48.036 --> 13:49.083
"Ivah!

13:50.455 --> 13:51.923
Precious memories.

13:52.123 --> 13:54.342
Just keep vacuuming.
Just keep vacuuming.

13:54.542 --> 13:55.464
Come on!

14:03.092 --> 14:04.093
We need to get higher.

14:04.302 --> 14:06.976
Yeah, especially you
because you're short.

14:07.180 --> 14:08.432
Mabel! Up there.

14:13.936 --> 14:18.316
What cute little thing are you off to,
you cute little cutey-face?

14:18.524 --> 14:22.745
I'm going to annihilate
my archenemy's entire family!

14:22.945 --> 14:25.118
Oh. Okay!

14:25.323 --> 14:26.700
(WEAKLY) Yay!

14:30.620 --> 14:31.792
He's heading to shrink Stan!

14:31.996 --> 14:33.794
Oh, flying discount dollar,

14:33.998 --> 14:37.218
if only you could fly us back
to the Mystery Shack.

14:37.418 --> 14:38.635
Maybe it can.

14:43.674 --> 14:45.426
(GASPS)

14:45.635 --> 14:47.683
MY SKY-high prices!

14:47.887 --> 14:49.514
DIPPER: Yeah!
MABEL: Wh00-h00!

14:49.722 --> 14:52.441
Down there!

14:52.600 --> 14:53.726
<i>MABEL: 'lay!
DIPPER: Whoa:!</i>

14:53.935 --> 14:55.653
To the Mystery Shack!

14:55.853 --> 14:56.729
(SHOUTS)

14:56.938 --> 14:58.360
<i>DIPPER: Yeah: Whoa-hoe:
MABEL: Yeah:!</i>

14:58.564 --> 15:01.067
BOTH: Oh! Yeah!

15:03.820 --> 15:05.788
We're just in time.

15:05.947 --> 15:07.995
- But how are we going to stop him?
-(PECKING)

15:08.199 --> 15:09.746
(SCREAMS) Shoo! Ah!

15:09.951 --> 15:13.626
(DIPPER GRUNTING)

15:13.830 --> 15:15.707
Leave that to Mabel!

15:15.915 --> 15:16.791
(LAUGHING)

15:16.999 --> 15:19.468
(HUMMING)

15:19.669 --> 15:22.969
I'm coming for you, Stanford. Ow!

15:24.465 --> 15:26.183
I'm sorry, gummy friend!

15:26.384 --> 15:27.636
It's for the greater good.

15:27.844 --> 15:30.097
Ow! One of those
infernal Gummy Koalas

15:30.304 --> 15:32.853
has gotten into my perfect hair!

15:33.057 --> 15:35.560
I can't defeat Stan looking like this!

15:37.979 --> 15:40.277
Whoo! Whoo-ee!

15:40.481 --> 15:42.404
Quick. Get in front and I'll re-grow you.

15:42.608 --> 15:45.908
Okay. Wait, you're gonna grow
us back to equal height, right?

15:46.112 --> 15:47.785
Dipper! That doesn't matter right now!

15:47.989 --> 15:49.832
Well, if it doesn't matter
then why don't you just do it?

15:50.032 --> 15:51.955
Argh! Why are you acting so weird?

15:52.160 --> 15:54.879
Why can't you just accept
that I'm a little bit taller than you?

15:55.079 --> 15:56.581
Oh, I'm acting weird?

15:56.789 --> 15:59.212
You're the one
who keeps calling me names and stuff!

15:59.417 --> 16:02.136
- Oh, what? You mean like Little...
- Don't say it!

16:02.336 --> 16:04.509
GIDEON: Little Dipper.

16:04.714 --> 16:05.715
'Ah!

16:05.923 --> 16:10.429
I dare say you would've defeated me,
if it wasn't for your sibling bickering.

16:12.805 --> 16:16.981
The Shack is mine, Stanford Pines!

16:17.185 --> 16:20.860
BOTH: No!

16:21.022 --> 16:24.492
Well, well, Stanford, it appears
I've finally gotten the best of...

16:24.692 --> 16:25.693
Huh?

16:25.902 --> 16:26.903
What!

16:27.111 --> 16:30.035
All right,
something's definitely different here.

16:30.239 --> 16:31.240
(ALL GRUNT)

16:31.449 --> 16:33.042
DIPPER: Whoa!

16:33.242 --> 16:34.539
Tell me where Stan is!

16:34.744 --> 16:36.417
Never! You'll never find Stan.

16:36.621 --> 16:38.248
On the second door
to the left down the hall.

16:38.456 --> 16:40.879
Wait, why did I say that?

16:41.042 --> 16:44.672
Stanford, I'm coming for ya!

16:44.879 --> 16:47.302
(ALL GRUNTING)

16:50.092 --> 16:51.935
I guess I kind of Soosed that one up,
didn't I?

16:52.136 --> 16:53.137
It's not your fault, Soos.

16:53.346 --> 16:55.769
I'm the guy who put together
that shrinking device.

16:55.973 --> 16:58.601
I guess it's just...
You kept teasing me, Mabel.

16:58.809 --> 17:02.564
Like, all day. What was that all about?

17:02.730 --> 17:06.233
I guess it's that,
you're better at me at, like, everything.

17:06.442 --> 17:09.116
And you always rub it in my face.

17:09.319 --> 17:13.040
Chess, checkers, ping pong.

17:13.241 --> 17:17.838
I guess I finally felt like I was winning
at something for once.

17:18.037 --> 17:20.756
Oh, man, now I feel like a big jerk.

17:20.957 --> 17:23.506
Don't you mean a little jerk?

17:23.709 --> 17:25.837
- Oh.
-(BOTH LAUGH)

17:26.045 --> 17:28.764
All right, I walked into that one.
Are we cool?

17:28.965 --> 17:30.763
- We're cool.
- Am I cool?

17:30.967 --> 17:33.390
- You're cool, Soos.
- Yes!

17:36.055 --> 17:37.022
(GASPS)

17:37.223 --> 17:38.440
Stanford!

17:38.641 --> 17:39.517
Oh, hi, Gideon!

17:39.725 --> 17:42.399
I've been looking for someone
to try out my new mirror maze.

17:42.603 --> 17:46.073
Then again, you're an idiot.
That's the end of the sentence.

17:46.274 --> 17:47.571
You come back here!

17:47.733 --> 17:49.235
STAN: Try and find me, twerp.

17:49.402 --> 17:52.656
(STAN LAUGHING)

17:52.863 --> 17:55.867
Let's get that flashlight
before Gideon gets Stan.

17:56.075 --> 17:58.919
There it is!

17:59.120 --> 18:01.794
(ALL GRUNTING)

18:01.998 --> 18:05.047
Whoa! His hair's so shiny.

18:05.251 --> 18:07.424
No! Don't look directly at it!

18:07.628 --> 18:11.633
This neck is really squishy.
Look! I'm making fat angels!

18:11.841 --> 18:14.219
Ew! Termites!

18:14.427 --> 18:17.556
Tell my story!

18:17.763 --> 18:18.810
Oh.

18:20.308 --> 18:21.810
Hey, there you are!

18:22.018 --> 18:25.238
Thought you could get away
from me, eh, corn chip?

18:33.195 --> 18:34.162
[3511

18:34.363 --> 18:36.331
BOTH: Ah!

18:36.532 --> 18:40.662
Ahhh!

18:40.870 --> 18:42.497
(STAN LAUGHING)

18:42.705 --> 18:43.831
[[511

18:44.040 --> 18:47.920
Hey, watch the merchandise!

18:48.127 --> 18:52.633
(GRUNTING)

18:53.257 --> 18:54.554
You little troll!

18:54.759 --> 18:58.605
These mirrors cost me 10...
I mean, 25... Five hun...

18:58.804 --> 19:01.307
$500 each.
And you're paying for all of 'em!

19:01.515 --> 19:04.064
<i>Au</i> contraire, it will be you who pays!

19:04.268 --> 19:05.645
Grunkle Stan is doomed!

19:05.853 --> 19:07.901
Not completely doomed! To his armpit!

19:08.105 --> 19:11.154
- Uh-uh.
- Just, come on!

19:11.359 --> 19:12.781
Whoa! What is that thing?

19:12.985 --> 19:16.615
Finally, after all these years,
after every humiliation!

19:16.822 --> 19:19.996
Your business, your family,
everything will finally be mine!

19:20.201 --> 19:22.078
You have no one to protect you now!

19:22.286 --> 19:26.666
Prepare for the wrath of Gideon Glee...
Gideon Glee...

19:26.874 --> 19:30.469
(LAUGHING)

19:30.670 --> 19:34.846
Uh. I don't even know
how to respond to this.

19:35.049 --> 19:37.143
No! Stop it!

19:37.343 --> 19:40.722
Look, kid.
I think this rivalry thing is getting to you.

19:40.930 --> 19:44.605
Ha. I understand, I mean,
I'm a formidable foe, what can I say.

19:44.809 --> 19:47.403
[[511

19:47.603 --> 19:50.277
Hey, now, come on.
You'll get me one of these days.

19:50.481 --> 19:54.236
Maybe, you know, run your evil plan
by some friends next time, huh?

19:54.443 --> 19:58.664
Workshop it.
But first get your issues in order there.

20:02.827 --> 20:05.455
Up, up. Over the carpet, there we go,

20:05.663 --> 20:08.212
around the end table and out the door.

20:08.416 --> 20:09.759
BOTH: Whoa!

20:12.169 --> 20:13.341
My light!

20:13.546 --> 20:15.924
You're the light of my life, too, pal.

20:16.132 --> 20:17.099
Whoo!

20:17.299 --> 20:18.346
Freak show.

20:21.345 --> 20:25.145
- After you.
- It's okay, you can go first if you want...

20:32.732 --> 20:35.451
Hey, you let me keep
my extra millimeter!

20:35.651 --> 20:36.573
You earned it.

20:36.777 --> 20:39.951
- Aw, thanks, "Little brother."
- Stop it.

20:40.156 --> 20:42.124
Guess we should destroy this thing.

20:42.324 --> 20:45.954
You know, so it doesn't fall
into the wrong hands and junk.

20:46.162 --> 20:49.632
Seems like the smart thing to do.

20:49.832 --> 20:51.834
MABEL: Die! Die!

20:52.042 --> 20:53.885
SOOS: There you dudes are!

20:54.086 --> 20:55.588
I've been trying to get your attention!

20:57.673 --> 21:00.267
- Glue.
- Lots of glue.

21:00.468 --> 21:03.563
Oh, son, don't you mind
that Stanford Pines.

21:03.763 --> 21:06.141
You'll get your revenge
one of these days.

21:06.307 --> 21:08.776
No! It's not just about revenge!

21:08.976 --> 21:11.980
I want that shack. The physical building.

21:12.188 --> 21:13.235
But why?

21:13.439 --> 21:17.114
Because it holds a secret
you couldn't possibly imagine.

21:17.318 --> 21:19.741
(EVIL LAUGH)

21:19.945 --> 21:21.572
Uh, sweetie, you want some ice cream?

21:21.781 --> 21:23.203
Did you pick out all the nuts?

21:23.407 --> 21:24.954
Mmm-hmm.

21:25.159 --> 21:26.035
(SNORTING)

21:26.243 --> 21:28.541
(MANIACAL LAUGHTER)

21:28.746 --> 21:29.918
Little more?

21:30.122 --> 21:32.500
(MANIACAL LAUGHTER)

21:32.708 --> 21:34.927
GIDEON: That's good.

21:35.127 --> 21:36.925
(DOORBELL RINGS)

21:37.129 --> 21:39.678
Mr. Pines, I'm from the Winninghouse
Coupon Savers Contest

21:39.882 --> 21:42.431
and you are our big winner!

21:42.635 --> 21:44.558
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

21:44.762 --> 21:47.641
I guess we'll have to give the prize
to our runner-up winner.

21:47.848 --> 21:52.103
"Fiddleford H. McGucket."

21:52.311 --> 21:55.110
How would you like $10,000,000?

21:55.314 --> 21:57.408
It's my dream come true!

22:00.486 --> 22:02.238
Cross this town off our list.
